# Prompt: Generate Fake Test Documents for RAG Chatbot

---

## Context (Read This First)

I am building and testing an enterprise RAG (Retrieval-Augmented Generation) chatbot for a manufacturing company. The system has **14 departments**, each with a specific document domain and security level. I need you to generate **realistic-looking fake documents** (in Vietnamese, or mixed Vi/En as appropriate) to use as test data. The documents do not need to be real — they just need to look and feel authentic enough to test retrieval, classification, and Q&A.

The system can ingest: **PDF, Word (.docx), Excel (.xlsx), CSV, plain text (.txt), Markdown (.md), and images (.jpg, .png)**.

For each document below, I will tell you:

- **File format** to produce
- **Department** it belongs to
- **Security level** (`public` / `internal` / `confidential`)
- **Content requirements** (what data/structure it must contain)
- **Test questions** the chatbot must be able to answer from it (so make sure the answers are in the document)

---

